  {
    "client_msg_id": "65b0e1d4-4c3c-4672-9885-70fe99a0a175",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I'd like to dispel any impression that I'm a debugger guy: <https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=11854319#11855294;> <https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=11048633#11052363>\n\nWatches (and, I suspect, time travel debugging) are unused in gdb by pretty much everyone I know (even the debugger guys) because they're too slow. Some features just have too much impedance mismatch with the \"debugger way\". They'd be orders of magnitude simpler to support if you just dump a trace of an execution and browse it after the fact. You lose the ability to change programs when they hit an error. But I don't see too many people using debuggers like that either.",
    "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
